From: Easwar Hariharan <eahariha@linux.microsoft.com>
Date: Mon, 7 Jul 2025 15:03:32 -0700
Subject: net/smc: convert timeouts to secs_to_jiffies()
Git-commit: 4814f9110ec6b7b2a25ec0c397f996ce34d31115
References: jsc#PED-14951
Patch-mainline: v6.17-rc1

Commit b35108a51cf7 ("jiffies: Define secs_to_jiffies()") introduced
secs_to_jiffies().  As the value here is a multiple of 1000, use
secs_to_jiffies() instead of msecs_to_jiffies to avoid the multiplication.

This is converted using scripts/coccinelle/misc/secs_to_jiffies.cocci with
the following Coccinelle rules:

@depends on patch@
expression E;
@@

-msecs_to_jiffies(E * 1000)
+secs_to_jiffies(E)

-msecs_to_jiffies(E * MSEC_PER_SEC)
+secs_to_jiffies(E)

Signed-off-by: Easwar Hariharan <eahariha@linux.microsoft.com>
Reviewed-by: Dust Li <dust.li@linux.alibaba.com>
Reviewed-by: Guangguan Wang <guangguan.wang@linux.alibaba.com>
Link: https://patch.msgid.link/20250707-netdev-secs-to-jiffies-part-2-v2-1-b7817036342f@linux.microsoft.com
Signed-off-by: Jakub Kicinski <kuba@kernel.org>
Acked-by: Steffen Jaeckel <sjaeckel@suse.de>

---
 net/smc/af_smc.c | 3 +--
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 2 deletions(-)

